    "Factors important for radiationThe feature importances combined from three considered models (LASSO regression, Random Forest, and XGBoost) can serve as a tool to understand the influence of different Geospace environment factors on the effective dose rates measured.",
    "In this subsection, we provide a qualitative assessment of the feature importance analysis and the corresponding physics implications.The feature importance analysis for all three models indicates that geomagnetic cutoff rigidity and the GPS altitude represent the two most important features.",
    "This is understandable, as both quantify the energetic particle access to the Earth's atmosphere and, therefore, the flux of secondary cosmic ray particles.",
    "In particular, geomagnetic cutoff rigidities indicate the minimum momentum per charge for the particle to access the region, which is near-zero at the geomagnetic poles up to ∼15 GV for some near-equatorial regions [28].",
